{
  "stem": "2938.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Everybody got a shower.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody washed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they segregated us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Young people in one side, old people on the other side, women on another side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Children-- there weren't too many children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So anyways, we were segregated and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they took us in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "From the 900 people-- I don't know how many-- maybe 800 of us, they took us into the barracks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They took us into the-- no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "First, everybody got undressed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They took away all the clothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Everybody should give them the diamond, the gold, all the belongings, what we had.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Everybody-- we didn't have nothing anyways.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So we went out naked from there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They gave us uniforms, special uniforms.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They dressed us up, and they took us to the barracks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I came to barrack nine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Others went to other barracks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Next day, they talk us out and they gave everybody a number.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Me, they gave B3303.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And everybody got a number.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They took the name--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The address, the birth, and the city, and everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They kept records on everything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you were alive now, and they kill you an hour later, they hold record on everybody.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Nazis, the Germans kept records of everybody.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the camp-- the-- the managers of the camps were prisoners, German prisoners, but the Nazis kept the records, all the records.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they gave everybody a number.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after the number, it was finished, it started, next day, a segregation.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They put out-- so it wasn't only the Kielce people there, but people from a neighboring city near Kielce.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were ammunition factories-- Starachowice, Skarzysko, Blyzin, and other camps near-- us, where the people-- everybody got a number and they start segregating.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So certain people, they put to the left.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
